{{Spanish name|'''Corripio'''|'''Ahumada'''}}
{{Infobox Christian leader | type = Cardinal | honorific-prefix = [[His Eminence]] | name = Ernesto Corripio y Ahumada | honorific-suffix = | title = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Mexico|Primate Archbishop of Mexico]] | image = Ernesto_Corripio_y_Ahumada.png | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | church = | archdiocese = | province = | metropolis = | diocese = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Mexico|Mexico]] | see = Mexico | enthroned = | appointed = 19 July 1977 | term_end = 29 September 1994 | predecessor = [[Miguel Darío Miranda y Gómez]] | successor = [[Norberto Rivera Carrera]] | other_post = | ordination = 15 October 1942 | ordained_by = [[Pope Pius XII]] | consecration = 19 March 1953 | consecrated_by = [[Octaviano Márquez y Toriz]] | cardinal = 30 June 1979 | rank = Cardinal-Priest | previous_post = {{unbulleted list|[[Roman Catholic Diocese of Tampico|Bishop of Tampico]] (1956 – 1967)}}{{unbulleted list|[[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Antequera, Oaxaca|Archbishop of Antequera]] (1967 – 1977)}}{{unbulleted list|[[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Puebla de los Angeles|Archbishop of Puebla de los Angeles]] (1977 – 1994)}} <!---------- Personal details ----------> | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1919|06|29}} | birth_place = [[Tampico, Tamaulipas|Tampico]], [[Tamaulipas]], [[Mexico]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|2008|04|10|1919|06|29|df=yes}} | death_place = La Noria, [[Xochimilco]], [[Mexico]] | buried = | nationality = [[Mexico|Mexican]] | religion = [[Roman Catholic]] | residence = | parents = | occupation = | profession = | alma_mater = [[Pontifical Gregorian University]] | motto = Nuestro Vivir es Cristo | signature = Corripio Signat0001.jpg <!---------- Sainthood ----------> | feast_day = | venerated = | saint_title = | beatified_date = | beatified_place = | beatified_by = | canonized_date = | canonized_place = | canonized_by = | attributes = | patronage = | shrine = | suppressed_date = <!---------- Other ----------> | other = | coat_of_arms = Coat of Arms of Ernesto Corripio.svg }} {{Infobox cardinal styles | cardinal name = Ernesto Corripio Ahumada | dipstyle = His Eminence | offstyle = Your Eminence | See = Mexico City ([[emeritus]]) | image = Coat of Arms of Ernesto Corripio.svg | image_size = 200px }} '''Ernesto Corripio y Ahumada''' (June 29, 1919 – April 10, 2008) was a [[cardinal (Catholicism)|cardinal]] of the [[Roman Catholic Church]]. He was [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Mexico|Archbishop of Mexico]] in [[Mexico City]] (1977–1994) and was [[primate (bishop)|Primate]] of [[Mexico]]. In the [[Papal consistory|consistory]] of June 30, 1979 in [[Vatican City]] [[Pope John Paul II]] created him [[cardinal (Catholicism)|Cardinal Priest]] of the [[titular church]] of ''[[Blessed Virgin Mary|Mary Immaculate of Tiburtino]]''.
==Life== Corripio y Ahumada was [[ordained]] to the [[Priesthood (Catholic Church)|priesthood]] on October 15, 1942. He served as a diocesan priest in his hometown of Tampico for ten years. On December 27, 1952, [[Pope Pius XII]] appointed him [[auxiliary bishop]] of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Tampico|Diocese of Tampico]]. On March 19, 1953, he was consecrated [[titular bishop]] of Zapara. On February 25, 1956, he became [[Bishop]] of the diocese.
[[Pope Paul VI]] elevated Corripio y Ahumada on July 25, 1967 to Archbishop of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Antequera|Antequera]] in the state of [[Oaxaca]]. On March 11, 1976, he was transferred to become Archbishop of the [[Archdiocese of Puebla de los Angeles]] in the state of [[Puebla]]. The Pope transferred Corripio y Ahumada once again on July 19, 1977 to the post of Archbishop of Mexico.
Upon assuming the papal throne, Pope John Paul II appointed Corripio y Ahumada a member of the [[College of Cardinals]]. He was a member of various departments of the [[Roman Curia]] while serving his archdiocese.
He retired on September 29, 1994.<ref>[http://www.fiu.edu/~mirandas/bios-c.htm#Corripio The Cardinals of the Holy Roman Church - Biographies<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
He died on April 10, 2008 in his house in La Noria, Xochimilco in Mexico City, after complications related to deep thrombosis in his left arm. He is buried in the crypt of [[Mexico City Metropolitan Cathedral]].
