{{Taxobox | name = Tilapia lake virus | image = | image_alt = | image_caption = | virus_group = v | ordo = | familia = | genus = | species = '''''Tilapia lake virus''''' }}
'''Tilapia lake virus''', or '''TiLV''', is a virus infecting populations of [[tilapia]].<ref>http://mbio.asm.org/content/7/2/e00431-16</ref> The virus is responsible for decimation of some populations and was only discovered recently.<ref>https://www.theatlantic.com/science/archive/2016/04/a-new-fish-virus-shows-how-vulnerable-our-food-supplies-are/476847/</ref>
==Discovery==
The paper discovering was submitted in 2014.<ref>http://jcm.asm.org/content/52/12/4137</ref> The virus is distantly related to the Influenza C virus and is likely a novel orthomyxovirus.<ref>http://influenza-news.blogspot.com/2016/04/tilapia-lake-virus.html</ref>
==Symptoms== Reported symptoms of infected fish include reddened skin, inflammation of organs including the eyes and brain, liver damage,<ref>http://technology.inquirer.net/47540/scientists-identify-deadly-tilapia-virus</ref> and eventual organ failure and death. The mortality rate is about 80-100% of infected fish.<ref>{{cite journal |pmid=25232154 | doi=10.1128/JCM.00827-14 | volume=52 | title=Identification of a novel RNA virus lethal to tilapia | pmc=4313277 | year=2014 | journal=J. Clin. Microbiol. | pages=4137–46 | last1 = Eyngor | first1 = M | last2 = Zamostiano | first2 = R | last3 = Kembou Tsofack | first3 = JE | last4 = Berkowitz | first4 = A | last5 = Bercovier | first5 = H | last6 = Tinman | first6 = S | last7 = Lev | first7 = M | last8 = Hurvitz | first8 = A | last9 = Galeotti | first9 = M | last10 = Bacharach | first10 = E | last11 = Eldar | first11 = A}}</ref>
==Transmission==
It is believed to be waterborne, infesting populations around the world.
